HEADWORD: Pritch
<hw>Pritch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Prick</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sharp-pointed instrument;
also, an eelspear.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pique; offense.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>D.
Rogers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pritchel</ent>⟦br⟧
